ZH: 我昨晚梦游到了一个陌生的城市。
EN: Last night, I sleepwalked to a strange city.

ZH: 他最近几个月频繁梦游。
EN: He has been sleepwalking frequently in the past few months.

ZH: 在梦游状态下，他会做出各种奇怪的动作。
EN: In the state of sleepwalking, he would make all sorts of strange movements.

ZH: 她有时会梦游到楼下去偷吃冰淇淋。
EN: Sometimes, she sleepwalks downstairs to secretly eat ice cream.

ZH: 我小时候曾经梦游到了海边。
EN: When I was a child, I once sleepwalked to the seaside.

ZH: 我从来没有经历过梦游的情况。
EN: I have never experienced sleepwalking.

ZH: 他梦游的时候，全身都是冷汗。
EN: When he sleepwalks, his whole body is covered in cold sweat.

ZH: 他对于自己的梦游状态毫无察觉。
EN: He is completely unaware of his sleepwalking state.

ZH: 老人说，梦游是因为前世积下的业障。
EN: The old man said that sleepwalking is due to karmic retribution from past lives.

ZH: 梦游的人往往在半夜醒来，不知道自己所处的位置。
EN: Sleepwalkers often wake up in the middle of the night, unaware of their location.

ZH: 我担心他梦游时会发生意外。
EN: I am worried that something might happen to him during sleepwalking.

ZH: 这个小孩的梦游已经持续了一个月。
EN: This child's sleepwalking has been going on for a month.

ZH: 她的梦游问题需要专业的医生来治疗。
EN: Her sleepwalking issue requires treatment from a professional doctor.

ZH: 在梦游的时候，他会有一种超乎常人的敏感度。
EN: When sleepwalking, he has an extraordinary level of sensitivity.

ZH: 他梦游时经常说着让人听不懂的话。
EN: He often talks in incomprehensible words while sleepwalking.

ZH: 梦游可能是一种内心压力释放的方式。
EN: Sleepwalking might be a way to release inner stress.

ZH: 梦游是一种睡眠障碍症状。
EN: Sleepwalking is a symptom of sleep disorder.

ZH: 我的小侄子昨晚又梦游了一次。
EN: My little nephew sleepwalked again last night.

ZH: 梦游中的人有时会走出家门，甚至到达街道上。
EN: People who sleepwalk sometimes walk out of their houses and even reach the streets.

ZH: 我不喜欢夜晚一个人梦游。
EN: I don't like sleepwalking alone at night.

ZH: 老师告诉我，梦游是一种相当常见的现象。
EN: The teacher told me that sleepwalking is a fairly common phenomenon.
